Licensing

Public domainPublic domainfalsefalse
This image of simple geometry is ineligible for copyright and therefore in the public domain, because it consists entirely of information that is common property and contains no original authorship.


This file shows the Singapore flag, national emblem, and national anthem protected by law. The regulations governing the use or display of the national flag for flagrant desecration are located in Chapter 3 of the "Singapore National Emblem, National Flag, and National Anthem Act", formulated by the Singapore National Emblem, National Flag, and National Anthem Committee. People who commit insults to the national flag, such as burning or tearing it up, will be fined at least 1,000 Singapore dollars. This is a non-copyright restriction.

This label does not indicate the copyright status of the attached works. The general copyright label is still required. For more information, please refer to License Terms.
